# TypeScript Safety

- Prefer explicit types at module boundaries; avoid implicit `any`.
- Use `import type` for type-only imports to keep runtime output clean.
- Prefer domain types from workspace packages (for example geometry/editor types) instead of ad hoc object shapes.
- Keep scene-related updates immutable unless a dedicated helper explicitly allows mutation.

## How to verify

1. Run `yarn test:typecheck`.
2. Run `yarn test:code` and check for `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` violations.
3. Spot-check changed imports and convert runtime imports to `import type` where appropriate.
